UPDATE control_load_history
SET status = 'FAILED', 
finish_timestamp = $$CurrentTimeStamp,
updated_at = $$CurrentTimeStamp
WHERE data_flow_name = 'DF_LOAD_dim_person_V3_ODS' AND status= 'RUNNING';

UPDATE control_load_history
SET status = 'SUCCEEDED', 
finish_timestamp = $$CurrentTimeStamp,
SRC_source_count =  $RST_DF_LOAD_dim_person_V3_ODS.SRC_dim_user.SourceCount  , 
SRC_process_count =  $RST_DF_LOAD_dim_person_V3_ODS.SRC_dim_user.ProcessCount  , 
SRC_target_count =  $RST_DF_LOAD_dim_person_V3_ODS.SRC_dim_user.TargetCount  , 
SRC_bad_count =  $RST_DF_LOAD_dim_person_V3_ODS.SRC_dim_user.BadCount  ,
TGT_source_count =   $RST_DF_LOAD_dim_person_V3_ODS.TGT_dim_person.SourceCount  , 
TGT_process_count =  $RST_DF_LOAD_dim_person_V3_ODS.TGT_dim_person.ProcessCount  , 
TGT_target_count  =  $RST_DF_LOAD_dim_person_V3_ODS.TGT_dim_person.TargetCount   , 
TGT_bad_count =  $RST_DF_LOAD_dim_person_V3_ODS.TGT_dim_person.BadCount   ,
updated_at = $$CurrentTimeStamp
WHERE data_flow_name = 'DF_LOAD_dim_person_V3_ODS' AND status= 'RUNNING'

INSERT INTO control_load_history (data_flow_name, status, start_timestamp, created_at)
VALUES ('DF_LOAD_dim_person_V3_ODS', 'RUNNING', $$CurrentTimeStamp, $$CurrentTimeStamp);
